narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: i loved being able to blend and compare christian and judiac values. it helped me understand the principles of each with deeper analysis in practice.

Learned so much about Christian/Jewish law and rituals. Examined different opinions and readings of text and body. Bettered my writing and reading skills. Such an awesome examination of late antiquity/early christianity/rabbinic Judaism.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I loved the overall flow of the reading material/how it was ordered. I would have appreciated some grounding or ties historically/within a particular timeline. Additionally, the overall course structure was more chill and I find myself being a student who needs harsh deadlines with reminders/emphasis from the instructor.

I loved all of the readings. Loved the reading response structure. Appreciated the flexibility of topic for the final paper. Seminars/discussion were always a high point of my week because Prof. Bick is so good at offering new perspectives and challenging conventional ways of reading a topic. I wonder if it could benefit from one or two more structured assignments.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: YES. Some incredible readings if you are interested in Jewish and Christian thought about the body, spirit, and soul. There's so much room for interpretation, philosophical entry, etc.

Totally! I learned so so much and think it would be really interesting material for anyone regardless of major. Prof. Bick provided tons of support and feedback throughout the class and always worked to facilitate student learning.
